summary: This FBI 302 form documents a digital review of evidence processed by CART (Computer Analysis and Response Team) for the Epstein case, listing device identifiers and counts of highly confidential images and videos containing nudity. The responsive material is stored on a 2TB hard drive at the FBI New York Field Office.

events.title: Digital Evidence Review Completion
events.description: A digital review of evidence processed by CART for images and videos related to the case was conducted, with responsive material marked as 'RESPONSIVE - HIGHLY CONFIDENTIAL'.

events.title: Document Drafting
events.description: The FBI 302 document was drafted, summarizing the results of the digital evidence review.

locations: New York, New York, United States
keyFacts: A digital review identified thousands of images and videos containing partial or full nudity across multiple devices, marked as 'RESPONSIVE - HIGHLY CONFIDENTIAL'.
Device NYC024329 contained 1,368 highly confidential images and 2 videos; NYC024353 contained 4,173 images and 368 videos; NYC024349 contained 13,422 images.
All responsive material is stored on a 2TB hard drive with evidence number 18 136 at the FBI New York Field Office.
The document is an FBI 302 form, which is a report of investigation, and contains child victim/witness identity information with restricted disclosure.
The review was completed on November 20, 2020, and the document was drafted on December 29, 2020.
